<h1><span id="Sicilian_Defence.2C_Najdorf_Variation"></span><span id="Sicilian_Defence,_Najdorf_Variation">Sicilian Defence, Najdorf Variation</span></h1>
<p>Moves:1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6.Bg5 e6 7.f4
</p><p>Again, Black has to make a strategic choice. Common moves are :
</p>
<dl><dd>7...Be7</dd>
<dd>7...Qc7</dd>
<dd>7...Nbd7</dd></dl><p>Two very sharp variations are seen at higher levels : 7...Qb6 (the Poisoned Pawn Variation) and 7...b5 (the Polugaevsky Variation).
</p>
